The paper presents novel algorithms for synthesizing reactive systems from declarative specifications using decision procedures for propositional formulas, quantified boolean formulas, and effectively propositional logic. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses optimization techniques and parallelization, which are relevant to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The focus on safety specifications and query learning suggests that the paper may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions interpolation, which is a technique used in Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL), making it a possible sub-category as well.
